During a press gaggle on Air Force One, Principal Deputy Press Secretary Josh Earnest and Deputy National Security Advisor Ben Rhodes discussed various topics. Earnest announced that members of the Senate are preparing to introduce legislation that would allow Americans with student loans to refinance at lower rates. They also discussed the meeting with President-elect Poroshenko of Ukraine and the ongoing situation in Ukraine. Rhodes mentioned that President Obama did not have plans to meet with President Putin, but that they would be in the same venue at the G7 Summit. They also discussed the possibility of providing lethal aid to Ukraine, sectoral sanctions on Russia, and the release of a video of the Bergdahl exchange. Additionally, they addressed questions about democratic movements around the world and the VA Secretary position.